The paper deals with a problem arising in the context of sparse optimization, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The problem involves the projection onto a set, which is a common theme in computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms (cs.DS). The fact that the problem is NP-hard suggests that it may also be related to complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
